    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Drain and rinse your <strong>green lentils </strong>in a <strong>sieve </strong>under <strong>cold running water</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-lentil-and-walnut-salad-with-pesto/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>chicken</strong> to a <strong>tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for an initial 8 min</p><p>(Doubled your protein? Do this in batches!)</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-lentil-and-walnut-salad-with-pesto/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Trim, then chop your <strong>green beans</strong> in half</p><p>Cut your <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-lentil-and-walnut-salad-with-pesto/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken has had 8 min, add the <strong>halved green beans</strong> to the tray</p><p>Return the tray to the oven for 7 min further</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-lentil-and-walnut-salad-with-pesto/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-lentil-and-walnut-salad-with-pesto/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the green beans have had 7 min, remove the tray from the oven and add your<strong> walnuts</strong></p><p>Return the tray to the oven for a final 3-5 min or until the walnuts are toasted and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk so they don't burn!</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-lentil-and-walnut-salad-with-pesto/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>sun-dried tomato pesto </strong>and <strong>balsamic vinegar </strong>in a large bowl with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>roasted green beans</strong>, <strong>halved cherry tomatoes </strong>and <strong>washed spinach </strong>with the <strong>drained green lentils </strong>and most of the <strong>toasted walnuts </strong>(save some for garnish!) and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>lentil & walnut pesto salad</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-lentil-and-walnut-salad-with-pesto/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Transfer the <strong>cooked chicken </strong>to a clean board and slice finely</p><p>Serve the <strong>lentil & walnut pesto salad</strong> with the <strong>sliced chicken</strong> on top</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>remaining toasted walnuts</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
